The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, spoke on the telephone about the federal disaster declaration for Hurricane Harvey and the historic flooding in Houston. He thanked the local media for their efforts in providing real-time information to those affected by the disaster. Pence mentioned that the declaration freed up federal resources, with over 8,500 officials on the ground and FEMA director present. President Trump and the First Lady planned to visit the affected areas to assess the progress of the response. Pence emphasized the President's hands-on approach and commitment to supporting the recovery efforts. He encouraged affected individuals to reach out to FEMA for assistance. Pence expressed sympathy for those affected and assured them that the administration and the American people stand with them. He pledged ongoing support for the recovery and rebuilding of southeast Texas.